      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is a museum-grade example of the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. The 13B-REW rotary engine exhibits stellar compression and retains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, providing a seamless power band without the typical vacuum-line degradation found in lesser examples. The five-speed manual transmission is tight, with no synchro wear, feeding power to the rear wheels via a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The lightweight chassis retains its original torsional rigidity, supported by an unmolested double-wishbone suspension system. This vehicle is free of any heat-cycling fatigue in the engine bay and presents in concours-ready condition, offering a visceral, analog driving experience that remains unmatched.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Garage kept. Full service history included. No accidents. Pristine interior and exterior. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
